title: Si va Seh Mardeh
content:
Si va Seh Mardeh (Persian: سي وسه مرده, also Romanized as Sī va Seh Mardeh and Sīow Seh Mardeh; also known as  Sūsehmard and Su Shehmard)[1] is a village in Yeylan-e Shomali Rural District, in the Central District of Dehgolan County, Kurdistan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 55, in 14 families.[2] The village is populated by Kurds.[3]
